<akn:akomaNtoso xmlns:akn="http://docs.oasis-open.org/legaldocml/ns/akn/3.0"><akn:act><akn:meta><akn:identification source="#cosilico"><akn:FRBRWork prescriptive="true" authoritative="true"><akn:FRBRuri value="/akn/us/usc/22/9226" /><akn:FRBRdate date="2025-12-31" name="retrieval" /><akn:FRBRauthor href="#us-congress" /><akn:FRBRcountry value="us" /></akn:FRBRWork><akn:FRBRExpression><akn:FRBRuri value="/akn/us/usc/22/9226/eng@2025" /><akn:FRBRdate date="2025-12-31" /><akn:FRBRauthor href="#cosilico" /><akn:FRBRlanguage language="en" /></akn:FRBRExpression><akn:FRBRManifestation><akn:FRBRuri value="/akn/us/usc/22/9226/eng@2025/main.xml" /><akn:FRBRdate date="2025-12-31" /><akn:FRBRauthor href="#cosilico" /></akn:FRBRManifestation></akn:identification></akn:meta><akn:body><akn:section eId="sec_9226"><akn:num>9226</akn:num><akn:heading>Travel sanctions</akn:heading><akn:content><akn:p>§ 9226. Travel sanctions
The Secretary of State may deny a visa to, and the Secretary of Homeland Security may deny entry into the United States of, any alien who is—(1) a designated person;

(2) a corporate officer of a designated person; or

(3) a principal shareholder with a controlling interest in a designated person.

(Pub. L. 114–122, title II, § 206, Feb. 18, 2016, 130 Stat. 108.)</akn:p></akn:content><akn:subsection eId="subsec_9226_1"><akn:num>(1)</akn:num><akn:content><akn:p>(1) a designated person;</akn:p></akn:content></akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_9226_2"><akn:num>(2)</akn:num><akn:content><akn:p>(2) a corporate officer of a designated person; or</akn:p></akn:content></akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_9226_3"><akn:num>(3)</akn:num><akn:content><akn:p>(3) a principal shareholder with a controlling interest in a designated person.</akn:p></akn:content></akn:subsection></akn:section></akn:body></akn:act></akn:akomaNtoso>